comments.author: royalfestus
comments.body: While I don't intend to be pessimistic, I believe that projects relying solely on their social media presence for crowdfunding may face challenges, especially if they do not actively pursue strong partnerships. In my opinion, it would be wise to wait for a few successful projects to gain momentum and attract funds before launching the new crowdfunding initiative. This approach will allow the money to circulate within the ecosystem and create a more favorable environment for their own project's success

comments.body: Quote from: royalfestus on July 19, 2023, 07:00:59 PMWhile I don't intend to be pessimistic, I believe that projects relying solely on their social media presence for crowdfunding may face challenges, especially if they do not actively pursue strong partnerships. In my opinion, it would be wise to wait for a few successful projects to gain momentum and attract funds before launching the new crowdfunding initiative. This approach will allow the money to circulate within the ecosystem and create a more favorable environment for their own project's successI couldn't agree any less, partnerships has proven, over the years, to be a better shoulder for new projects to leverage, the influence of already exisiting projects is the guarantee that these projects enjoy when they partner to offer a service.
